This paper deals with the problem of sparse signal recovery, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), signal processing (cs.SP), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and statistics (cs.SI). The use of random orthogonal matrices is also a common technique in these fields, further supporting these sub-categories.
